{
  "stem": "3874.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And this particular uncle, his wife, they had sent their daughter to England-- their daughter was, at the time, 15 years old, and they sent her with the children's transport.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And the daughter came-- came to family, who helped her parents get a visa to England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my uncle, at the time, was released from the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I still have a copy of the release certificate from-- from Buchenwald, which I keep with my memoirs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anyway, after they were released, I remember them coming over to our house and telling my parents, just leave.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Leave everything you've got here-- just leave.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You just don't know how bad it can be.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were also told, if they would talk about their experiences in Buchenwald, they would be immediately arrested.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they didn't even want to talk about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just wanted to say, just leave.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Leave everything.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, that time also, right after Kristallnacht-- possibly before-- the Germans, what they would do is, if Jews had a factory or store, they would put in one of their own cronies to start running it and take it over.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So basically, my father's factory, a man was installed called a [GERMAN], who basically was now the boss of the factory, and my father to report to him, and you know, he would take care of-- this German guy would take care of all the finances-- start decreasing the amount of money my father would get, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he no longer had control of the factory, either.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My father at the time, after my uncle had told him to leave-- just get, out because you don't know how bad it can get-- they decided-- well, at first they tried to get out.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
